  - m_Id: 173941240350527488
    m_Localized: 'Instructions:'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173941247283712000
    m_Localized: 'Recipe:'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173941254825070592
    m_Localized: 'Recipe:'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173941263549222912
    m_Localized: 'Instructions:'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173941269664518144
    m_Localized: 'Recipe:'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173941279684710400
    m_Localized: 'Instructions:'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173941670501568512
    m_Localized: Logic gates
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943009793167360
    m_Localized: Gate
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943222951890944
    m_Localized: Let's look at the different types of logic gates and find out how
      they work.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943266576846848
    m_Localized: 'NOT - inverting '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943373191860224
    m_Localized: "Try changing the values 1 and 0. Watch what happens\r\n to the
      lightbulb."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943386714296320
    m_Localized: 'They only work with two values: <color=#0b0><b> 0 </color>and <color=#0b0>1
      </b> </color> (off/on), which represents whether the electrical current is
      flowing there or not. '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943413314572288
    m_Localized: "These are simple \r\n\"electronic decision makers\" \r\nin a computer."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943433128464384
    m_Localized: 'What are logic gates? '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943456616566784
    m_Localized: 'AND - and at the same time '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943471430848512
    m_Localized: We can imagine it as <color=#0b0><b>two switches (inputs)</b></color>,
      whose state is evaluated by a <color=#0b0><b>logic gate</b></color>, and based
      on that it turns the <color=#0b0><b>lightbulb (output)</b></color> on or off.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943535943438336
    m_Localized: Symbol
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943547133841408
    m_Localized: "\"You get points  <b><color=#0b0>IF </b> </color>you complete task
      1<b><color=#0b0> OR </b></color>task 2, \r\nyou don't have to complete both.\u201D "
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943574937882624
    m_Localized: 'The lightbulb will shine <b><color=#0b0> if </b></color><b><color=#0b0>
      at least one </b></color>switch is on. '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943601995337728
    m_Localized: Symbol
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943630743097344
    m_Localized: 'XOR - either or '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943644550746112
    m_Localized: 'The lightbulb will shine <b><color=#0b0>if </b></color><b><color=#0b0>
      only one </b></color>switch is on. '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943660791091200
    m_Localized: "\u201CYou can have chocolate <b><color=#0b0>or</b></color> a piece
      of candy, but <b><color=#0b0>not both</b></color>.\u201D\r\n\r\n   "
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943670123417600
    m_Localized: Symbol
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943683289337856
    m_Localized: "Let's try it out \r\nin the game."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943725760860160
    m_Localized: Symbol
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943758308659200
    m_Localized: "\u201CYou can go outside <b><color=#0b0>ONLY IF </b> </color>you
      have a hat <b><color=#0b0> AND </b> </color>a jacket.\u201D "
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943773496233984
    m_Localized: 'The lightbulb will shine <b><color=#0b0>only when </b> </color><b><color=#0b0>
      both </b> </color>switches are on. '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943788574756864
    m_Localized: "Not has only <b><color=#0b0>one input</b></color> (switch) and
      simply \r\n<b><color=#0b0>flips it to the other position</b></color>. "
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173943813023354880
    m_Localized: 'OR - at least one is enough '
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944768162844672
    m_Localized: HDD and SSD
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944781404262400
    m_Localized: What are HDD and SSD?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944791327985664
    m_Localized: "When you save a photo, game, or document to your computer, it gets
      saved \r\non the <color=#0b0><b>disk</color></b> - that's <color=#0b0><b>long-term
      storage</color></b>. Unlike <color=#0b0><b>RAM</color></b>, the disk <color=#0b0><b><u>isn't
      erased</color></b></u> when you turn off the computer."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944803093008384
    m_Localized: 'There are two <color=#0b0><b>main types of disks</b></color>:'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944810521120768
    m_Localized: HDD and...
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944819043946496
    m_Localized: ... SSD
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944826501419008
    m_Localized: '<color=#0b0><b>HDD</b></color> is an older type.

      

      

      Inside
      it has <color=#0b0><b>spinning platters</b></color> and a read head, so it''s
      a bit like a record player. Because of this, it''s usually slower, can be heard,
      and is <color=#0b0><b>more sensitive to shocks</b></color>.

      

      

      Its
      advantage is that it often offers <color=#0b0><b>a lot of space</b></color>
      for a lower price.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944835410120704
    m_Localized: 'SSD is a <color=#0b0><b>newer type of disk</b></color>.

      

      

      It
      has no spinning parts, it works more like a <color=#0b0><b>large flash drive</b></color>.

      Therefore
      it is faster, quiet and usually more durable. The biggest advantage of SSD
      over HDD is exactly the <color=#0b0><b>speed</b></color>: the computer turns
      on faster with an SSD, programs and games load faster, and the whole computer
      feels smoother.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 173944845057019904
    m_Localized: "Let's try it out \r\nin the game."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
